getAnAnswer

public abstract GroundFact getAnAnswer(Fact question,
                                       ProofContext context)
Try to prove a single fact. If provable, returns what was proved; if not provable, returns null.

For example, if you pass in a variable fact, such as (legal xplayer ?x), you will get back either null or (e.g.) (legal xplayer noop).

Parameters:
question - The question ('fact') to prove.
context -
Returns:
An answer to the question, or null if not provable.
